[As of 20 Feb 2020, the case number at LSU has increased to 16 (https://www.wbrz.com/news/lsu-mumps-outbreak-grows-university-now-confirms-16-cases). There are also confirmed cases of mumps reported at the following:
- Grice Middle School in Hamilton Township, Mercer Township, New Jersey (https://philadelphia.cbslocal.com/2020/02/20/confirmed-case-of-mumps-at-grice-middle-school-in-hamilton-township/)
- William Penn, St. Georges Technical, Delaware (https://www.delawareonline.com/story/news/health/2020/02/20/health-department-investigating-3-cases-mumps-william-penn-st-georges-technical/4820857002/)
- North Charleston High School, South Carolina (https://www.live5news.com/2020/02/20/dhec-confirms-case-mumps-north-charleston-high-school/).
